div.p:
Tell me then, what is a little ſinne? Sin being an aberration

from the right way, meaſure me the true diſtance of that aberration, meaſure me the line that meaſures that distance;
               Omne quantum eſt diviſibile in ſemper diviſibilia. thou wilt finde a kinde of infiniteneſſe in it. For each line is infinitely diviſible.
